t looks like the `spring-boot-actuator` depends solely on `spring-boot`. In version 3.0, it includes classes that require `io.micrometer:micrometer-core`, which isn't pulled in transitively. If I directly test the `MetricsEndpoint`, there’s a risk of javac failures. However, I don’t need to cover everything. I think I should research the javap dependencies further to understand what’s really required for proper coverage and if anything else needs to be addressed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8i1pft3sdfISssSAOw4BgTCy|fc_01c15fe1b372cecd016a42ea2451e48196ba1d7a24458114c2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nv='3.0.0'\nbase='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-actuator/%s/'%v\nfor ext in ['jar','pom']:\n urllib.request.urlretrieve(base+f'spring-boot-actuator-{v}.{ext}', f'actuator.{ext}')\nprint('downloaded')\nPY\njar tf actuator.jar | grep -E 'org/springframework/boot/actuate/(metrics|health|env|beans|trace|observation|audit|info)' | head -80\njar tf actuator.jar | grep 'module-info' || true\njdeps -summary actuator.jar 2>/dev/null | head -50\nrm -rf \"$tmp\"", "timeout": 40}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 478, "output": 722, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21168, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782770200381, "responseId": "resp_01c15fe1b372cecd016a42ea19070c819692d6167e216ee8e7"}}
